<br>
What I would like to do is get to the point of having two events a week -- one goofy one, with no xp or loot to speak of, just fun, and one regular one (raid, hunt, FA camp).<br>
<br>
Goofy ones don't have to be ones where we make newbies.  They could also be surnaming parties, swap meets, language fairs, etc -- anything that's not focused on either xp and loot or helping others.<br>
<br>
Here's my question.  Would enough people come to a goof-off event on a weekend?  I know lots of people don't like to goof off when they have a chance to get in a group and go someplace cool for most of a day off -- it's ok to feel that way; it doesn't make you a p|-|^t |3\/\/7z d00d.  I just need to know, so I can plan events that people like coming to.<br>
<br>
I also understand that some people feel like guild events should be more serious (yes, we are serious -- stop making faces at me Kaymar, you'll make me laugh -- BWAHAHAHA! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) Ahem, I mean, some people might feel that hunts and FA camps are the only good guild events.  If you feel that way, vote for the last option.<br>
<br>
Also, please note:<br>
<br>
Saturday = 12 noon pacific, 3 eastern, 8pm UK, 9pm CET<br>
Sunday = 12 noon pacific, 3 eastern, 8pm UK, 9pm CET<br>
Weeknight = Monday through Thursday, 5pm-ish pacific, 8pm-ish eastern, late in the UK/Europe<br>
Friday = 5pm-ish pacific, 8pm-ish eastern, late in the UK and Europe but on a Friday so it's not that big of a deal<br>
<br>
Your opinion counts, so vote for the best choice -- I've only got five options here, so I know all the best choices aren't going to be covered.  I know some people are always going to be unable to make it, but I want to have events at the best possible times -- and ENOUGH events so that most people can make at least some of them.</FONT><FORM method=post action="http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsevents.processVote?topicID=558.topic"><table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 width="55%"><tbody><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="1"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>I would go to a goof off event on a Saturday.</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="2"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>I would go to a goof off event on a Sunday.</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="3"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>I don't want to go to a goof off event unless it's on a weeknight.</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="4"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>I don't want to go to a goof off event unless it's on a Friday.</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="5"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Events should be FA camps or raids and nothing else.</FONT></td></tr></tbody></table><P><input type=submit value="Vote"><a HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsevents.showMessage?topicID=558.topic&pollResults=on><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Show results</FONT></A> <p><font color=green face="ARIAL, HELVETICA, LUCIDA SANS"><B>Gwion Llewellyn</B></font><BR> Level, um, 40<BR>"But we have come to the Oasis of Marr searching for wives!"<BR>
